"{\"uid\": \"horseandhound.co.uk-news-olympic-dressage-gold-jessica-von-bredow-wendl-tsf-dalera-bb-867428\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Jessica von Bredow-Werndland TSF Dalera BB kept theirOlympiccrown firmly in place as they danced to individual gold in the dressage grand prix freestyle with a +90% score.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 171, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 7, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their French-themed freestyle music was a perfect fit for Paris.\", \"from\": 173, \"to\": 237, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 231, \"end\": 236, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1713880012633365e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The crowd clapped them through the closing stages to the sound of \\u00c9dith Piaf, as this prolific partnership left nothing to regret in theOlympic dressagearena.\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 304, \"end\": 314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"score\": 0.9999999997958184, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"\\u00c9dith Piaf\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00c9dith_Piaf\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The world number ones and reigning European Champions arrived in Paris unbeaten in their last 35 international outings - a winning streak that started when they claimed individual gold in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 594, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 465, \"end\": 470, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1713880012633365e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9968842363986326, \"rank\": 0.003125478823036211, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They leave as only the fourth combination to ever defend an Olympic individual dressage gold medal, landing victory on 90.09% and the only combination to break the 90% barrier at these Games.\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She knows everything.\", \"from\": 788, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's the most intelligent horse I have ever had,\\\" said an emotional Jessica, who rides this 17-year-old doyenne for B\\u00e9atrice A. Buerchler-Keller and Micaela Werndl.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She was 1000% with me.\", \"from\": 978, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She had no ear or eye anywhere else than me.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She was listening so carefully and she really showed me that that's what she wants to do.\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1136, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is why it makes me so emotional because I do not know if I will ever get a horse like her\\u2026 she is out of this world.\\\"\", \"from\": 1137, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As they exited the arena after their test, Jessica wiped a tear from her eye.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1306, \"end\": 1313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time she stepped onto the podium to receive her Olympic dressage gold medal, the tears were flowing freely.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am overwhelmed and exhausted.\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I had to cry too much today,\\\" said Jessica, reflecting on the difference she felt performing today as an individual compared to the pressure of riding as team anchor yesterday.\", \"from\": 1490, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1525, \"end\": 1532, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Today I woke up and I thought, 'it's all about trust'.\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1723, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are enough.\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1738, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can trust myself.\", \"from\": 1739, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can trust Dalera, I can trust us and it's about letting go.\", \"from\": 1759, \"to\": 1820, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This was a mental game change from yesterday to today.\", \"from\": 1822, \"to\": 1877, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not change anything about the equipment, or about Dalera - about anything.\\\"\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 1959, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tapping her own head, she added: \\\"It was just in here [I needed] to let go, to trust and to tell her that she is enough.\\\"\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 2082, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jessica spent the time she was pregnant with her daughter to create this freestyle.\", \"from\": 2084, \"to\": 2167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2084, \"end\": 2091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was six weeks pregnant and listening to 'Non, Je ne regrette rien' walking on the beach in Spain with my husband.\", \"from\": 2169, \"to\": 2285, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"score\": 0.9848626176158343, \"rank\": 0.014131489624868484, \"text\": \"Spain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Spain\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I got goosebumps on my whole body and told him, 'this is the music - this is what I want to do',\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2286, \"to\": 2393, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This pair's bond has blossomed over the nine years they have spent together - Jessica has even been napping in the mare's stable here in Paris.\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2538, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2473, \"end\": 2480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"score\": 0.9999953895500637, \"rank\": 4.610471174996568e-06, \"text\": \"Jessica\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jessica_Buchanan\"}, {\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2537, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1713880012633365e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's a bond Jessica puts down to listening to the mare and being led by what the horse tells her.\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She tells me how long she wants to hack out or she tells me when she needs a canter - a wild canter on the galloping track - and she tells me when she wants to work.\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2804, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She is just too good for everyone,\\\" she said.\", \"from\": 2805, \"to\": 2850, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"She's so smart and so funny.\", \"from\": 2852, \"to\": 2881, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I wanted to sleep in the hammock today and she was just playing with me - she was so funny, cheeky and happy.\\\"\", \"from\": 2882, \"to\": 2992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She added: \\\"She knew today was the day and she just did it.\", \"from\": 2994, \"to\": 3053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have not enough time yet [to fully thank her], but I will continue to just thank her again and again and again, and kiss her and cuddle her.\", \"from\": 3054, \"to\": 3196, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I know that my husband, Franzi [my show groom], and the owner is with her and they will all just tell her that she's just amazing.\", \"from\": 3198, \"to\": 3329, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3223, \"end\": 3229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franzi\", \"score\": 0.9999999941114766, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Franzi\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franzi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Franzi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I will spoil her to the last day of her life.\\\"\", \"from\": 3330, \"to\": 3376, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their closest rival wasIsabell Werth, the world's most decorated Olympian, who re-wrote the lyrics ofMandyto \\\"Oh, Wendy\\\", in honour of her exceptional new ride.They scored 89.61% to put the pressure onthe remaining competitors.\", \"from\": 3378, \"to\": 3605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3443, \"end\": 3451, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999055385205, \"rank\": 9.445500914049259e-08, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's world championsLottie Fry and Glamourdale sealed bronzein this gripping finale to the Olympic dressage, with a score of 88.97%.\", \"from\": 3607, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3607, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9996498087175152, \"rank\": 0.000350096965134803, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You might also be interested in:        Stay in touch with all the news in the run-up to and throughout the major shows and events during 2025 and beyond with a Horse & Hound subscription.Subscribe todayfor all you need to know ahead of these major events, plus online reports on the action as it happens from our\\u00a0expert team of reporters\\u00a0and in-depth analysis in our special commemorative magazines.\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 4146, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3907, \"end\": 3920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_&_Hound\", \"score\": 0.9999999999877218, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Horse & Hound\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_&_Hound\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Horse_&_Hound\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Have a subscription already?Set up your\\u00a0unlimited website access now\", \"from\": 4147, \"to\": 4215, \"entities\": []}]}"